annotation.TEXT: Did I do it right?
Gotta be cautious of the parakoopa as I do this...
Easy enough.
1-ups are fair game, so I might as well get it.
And now, finally, at long last, I have earned the right to play the bonus game!
Ah, the midway gate. This is the only way to power up without scoring points (for now). Take advantage of it!
No, I shouldn't save the springboard for the goal, because it'll turn into a 100-point coin on me!
Now, I want to enter the boss door with 15 seconds left, but I can't just wait in front of it because of a patrolling Dry Bones, so I'll camp out in another spot...
Good thing the goal tape wasn't right at the top when the timer hit 1!
Argh! The last spike barely got me! But, I'm still alive! I can still do this!
Here comes a castle that can get tricky in a few places.
It's okay to stomp a Chuck once or twice. Plus, I really don't want baseballs sneaking up behind me later.
I could go underground, but this way's faster.
Just three Star World levels and Bowser's castle are all that remain...
Perfect! Now just beat Morton without any mistakes!
I'm so not hitting that star block. I'm sure I haven't gotten 30 coins, and if it spits out a coin, I'll get 10 points I don't want!

Now, I have two choices at this point: I can take the normal exit here, and go through the Donut Ghost House, or take this secret exit, and go through the Donut Secret House and Donut Secret 2. Both routes are worth the same number of forced points.
Now, I want to enter Iggy's room with 7 seconds left. So, to do that, I want to enter the smashing pillars' room with the timer at 44.
Note that my score is 500.
The first room isn't too hard...
Still gotta deal with Chuck, which could be tricky...
Bonk!
What if I were to bring a couple of springboards down there?
Whoa! It felt like I almost missed the goal tape there!
To be continued...
One level down, with just 50 points collected. Only 847 trillion more levels to go! (Actually, I think that number is just a little bit exaggerated!)
Finish!!! But, is 500 really the lowest I can score on a start to finish run of the game?
I had to wait for that guy to get away from the blocks so I wouldn't bonk him!
I'm not going to be an idiot here. I'll just go with the usual doors, 2 and 5.
Yes! Good thing I figured all this out ahead of time!
I'm sure I can score much lower than 1000 if I detour through the Vanilla Dome!
No, because the goal tape was near the bottom as the timer hit 1! Maybe next time.
Patience will get me past these guys.
Barf!
Fortunately, the game provides a handy dandy blue shell for me to use!
As such, one mistake could force me to start all over!
This Yoshi coin is tricky to avoid. Hmm...
I really don't want to reveal the pop-up mushroom here, but I also have to be careful not to bonk an overhead buzzy with a block.
All that's left is Bowser, and since points can't be earned during the fight, I only have to worry about defeating him! Since it's the same old fight as usual, I'm going to speed it up.
Hi, Yoshi! (Random useless fact: This annotation starts at 1:33.7 in the video.)
And now, we enter Capetown. However, capes are outlawed as they would come with 1000 points that I don't want!
However, this vertical shaft has a number of Dry Bones that want to screw me over!
Bye, Yoshi!
Two levels done. Only 846,999,999,999,999 levels to go! Fortunately, I won't have to play most of those!
Regardless of which path I chose, I should have 300 points upon entering Donut Plains 3.
Whoa! That was close! Simply getting knocked off Yoshi won't fail the challenge, but if I'd crashed into that guy at a bad angle, I might've stomped him for 200 points!
Hi, Yoshi! This awesome dinosaur will be very helpful for this mission!
...Or maybe jump over it. That works too!
...and this one too...
Yeah, this level was pretty run-of-the-mill.
Since we all know what the intro screen looks like, I'll just choose the 0 file to skip it.
Nothing too out of the ordinary right now.
Okay, now that Yoshi's up here, I also need one springboard.
Barf!
Hopefully Dry Bones won't be in the way when it's time for me to climb up!
Like this! Bye, Yoshi!
Hi, Yoshi!
Hmm... I'm only six stars away from a bonus game. Will I enter it here?
I'm not gonna try getting fancy here if I don't have to.
Careful! If I accidentally step on a pile of bones, it's back to Yoshi's Island 2 for me!
Only Bowser's Castle stands between me and victory now!
In any normal level, I can Yoshi jump for it if that happens, but here, I just have to hope I don't get unlucky!
Got to Iggy at the right time. Can I beat him at the right time?
Find out next time!
There's just one tricky part left...
Right here will do. (Random useless fact: This annotation starts at 13:37 in the video.)
Uh, oh. Yoshi can't climb vines! Whatever will I do?
Hi, Yoshi! Eat up the star and grow big and strong!
Okay, four levels down. Now there's just 846- *kicked in the nuts* Oooouuuugggghhhh...
I'll also want Yoshi for the next secret exit too, so I'll just go back and get another blue one in SW2.
Fortunately, the tape wasn't at the top this time either.
Hi, Yoshi! Long time no see!
Of course, why I didn't decide to go back for a Yoshi at this point is beyond me. (I must not've been thinking straight...)
And hopefully, I'll have a Yoshi for the next goal tape.
Simple enough.
I could've gotten the 1-up from the Yoshi block back there, but I kind of want to just get to the end of the level right now.
Keyhole exits are nice, since I don't have to worry about a time bonus with them!
Now I'll just simply fly up to the secret exit, keeping Yoshi with me for use in the next level.
That's three levels finished. Just 846,999,999,999,998 left! (Okay, that joke's starting to get old.)
Getting past the next mechakoopa will be tough. (Too bad I lost my power up, so I can't just sacrifice a hit.)
Now, I can fly past most of the level. Just make sure not to be in a bad spot when Yoshi decides to swallow!
Screw this mess! I'm going up and over!
In case you can't tell, I'm being extra cautious, as I'm doing this whole run in one shot without savestates anywhere (not even between levels)!
Kicking a shell is okay, as long as I grabbed it first.
Whoa, there! Almost went careening right into that Yoshi coin!
Make absolutely sure to hit the goal tape so that it doesn't become a 100-point coin.
Going up!
FF>>
Had good fortune with the goal tape again!
Now, boring water levels are boring, so I'm going to fast-forward most of this.
This springboard ought to come in handy!
First up is Yoshi's Island 2. Let's avoid as many points as possible!
Sweet!
Bonk!
Yay! Good thing nothing gives me points here!
Everyone's probably seen this scene about 846,999,999,999,997 times already, so I'll just FF it.
I'm taking the secret exit here, and to get to it without a cape... Bye, Yoshi!
Bonk!
I'll just skip to when time is nearly up.
Good. Now, let's get to that secret exit!
Okay, I want the secret exit in this level, but I'd rather not ditch Yoshi just to reach it. That would be inconvenient later.
Managed to avoid disaster there...
Eating stuff is usually okay, and regular floating coins are okay, but Yoshi coins must be avoided.
Okay, now!
Must... Resist... Power up... 1000 points... Bad...
Bonk! Knocking this guy off this way doesn't give me any points!
I think I'll take the secret exit from here.
Wait, how am I going to get to the next secret exit without killing Lakitu?

Now, I intend to take the normal exit here. Why not the secret exit? Because Star World 1 is loaded with blocks that I'd have to drill through, and I'd score way too many points (over 1000 just to reach the key)!
Yep, that was quick.
Nothing too special for the first half of the castle. Just avoid all the enemies.
Stay on this side. This way, if I do collide with something, I won't get points for it!
I want this level's secret exit as well, and that's where Yoshi will really come in handy!
And one final barf for good measure!
This level should be quick.
...nor is the second, as long as I'm not reckless.
YES!!!
I'll just gobble up any buzzies that are in my way.
It's possible to beat Iggy faster than that, but I wanted to go with a consistent timing method that I felt comfortable with.
Let's see if I timed this right...
For this Yoshi coin, just run right under it. Easy!
SMW challenge from Zeldara109: Clear the game from start to finish with as few points as possible.
I'll just slip under this here landmass...
Of course, you can always spit out your shell periodically to prevent a sudden death drop.
Okay, now I have to lure Chuck away from the goal, then sit next to the goal and wait for the timer to reach 1.
Bye, Yoshi!
Awesome! Now, we wait...
